66 SECTION 4.
67 Chapter 12 of Title 50 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to commissions
68 and other agencies, is amended by adding a new article to read as follows:
69 "ARTICLE 9
70 50-12-150.
71 As used in this article, the term:
72 (1) 'Board' means the Georgia Board for Artificial Intelligence.
73 (2) 'Governmental entity' means any department, agency, board, bureau, commission,
74 authority, county, municipal corporation, school system, or other political subdivision of
75 this state.
76 50-12-151.
77 (a) There is created the Georgia Board for Artificial Intelligence. The board shall consist
78 of 12 members to be appointed as follows:
79 (1) Four members appointed by the Governor;
80 (2) Four members appointed by the President of the Senate; and
81 (3) Four members appointed by the Speaker of the House of Representatives.
82 (b) The members of the board shall be individuals of recognized ability and achievement
83 from either public or private positions. All vacancies shall be filled for the unexpired term
84 by the original appointing official. Except as otherwise provided in subsection (c) of this
85 Code section, members shall serve for terms of four years and shall be eligible for
86 successive appointments by an appointing official. Any member with four consecutive
87 unexcused absences from regular monthly meetings may be removed from the board by the
88 appointing official.
