89 (c) To effect staggered terms of office for members of the board and effective with
90 members appointed for terms beginning in 2025, the Governor, the President of the Senate,
91 and the Speaker of the House of Representatives shall each appoint two members for
92 two-year terms of office, one member for a three-year term of office, and one member for
93 a one-year term of office. Thereafter, all members shall be appointed to serve four-year
94 terms of office.
95 (d) The board shall be assigned to the Georgia Technology Authority for administrative
96 purposes only, as prescribed in Code Section 50-4-3.
97 (e) The Governor shall designate a member to serve as the chairperson of the board for a
98 term ending on June 30 of the year following the appointment.
99 50-12-152.
100 (a) The board shall advise governmental entities through the publication of model
101 comprehensive artificial intelligence system usage plans as described in subsection (b) of
102 Code Section 50-1-14.
103 (b) The board, no later than January 1, 2026, and annually thereafter, shall submit to the
104 Governor, the President of the Senate, and the Speaker of the House of Representatives a
105 report detailing any recommendations along with the model comprehensive artificial
106 intelligence system usage plans required in subsection (a) of this Code section. Any reports
107 generated by the board shall be made available to the public on an annual basis by the
108 Georgia Technology Authority by posting such reports on the appropriate governmental
109 entity websites.
110 50-12-153.
111 (a) Board members shall receive no compensation for their services but shall be allowed
